# Insight article structure

When writing or editing `docs/insights/**/*.mdx`, pick **one article type** and apply its required sections. Do not stack redundant closings.

Reference articles: `langchain-vs-langgraph.mdx` (decision guide), `policy-governed-agent-runtime.mdx` (breakdown), `what-is-agentic-loop.mdx` (primer), `how-llm-work-under-the-hood.mdx` (explainer).

## Global rules

- **Hero banner + thumbnail (required).** Every insight needs a co-located PNG in the article folder, referenced twice:
  - **Thumbnail:** `image: ./{basename}.png` in frontmatter (insight list cards).
  - **Hero banner:** `![Short descriptive alt](./{basename}.png)` as the first content after frontmatter (before `#` title). Use the same file for both unless a separate `-thumb.png` is already in use in that folder.
  - **Naming:** prefer `{slug}.png`; match an existing `-thumb.png` in the folder if present.
  - **Style:** wide infographic (~16:9), G.A.I.N palette (navy grid background, blue / purple / orange accents), topic-specific diagram or metaphor. No em dashes in alt text.
  - **Create both references when authoring** — do not ship an insight without `image:` and the hero `![...]` line.
- **`<!-- truncate -->`** after the opening hook (before the main body).
- **`:::tip[THE CLAIM]`** near the top on all types except pure explainers that use stage takeaways only.
- **One opening hook** and **one closing hook**. Do not use `## Summary`, `## Key takeaways`, and `:::tip[TAKEAWAY]` together with the same bullets.
- End with **`:::info[Builds on]`** when the article links to frameworks or related insights (decision guides and primers).

## Article types

### 1. Decision guide

**When:** reader chooses between options (hosting, LangChain vs LangGraph, design intent router).

| Position | Required |
| --- | --- |
| Open | `:::tip[THE CLAIM]` + `## The bottom line first` (4-6 bullets) |
| Close | `## Key takeaways` (4-6 bullets) + `:::info[Builds on]` |
| Avoid | Long `## Summary` paragraph if Key takeaways exists |

**Examples:** `model-hosting-options-regulated-industries`, `langchain-vs-langgraph`, `design-intent-router`

### 2. Architecture breakdown

**When:** one system traced end-to-end (PGAR wire, RAG path, observability stack).

| Position | Required |
| --- | --- |
| Open | `:::tip[THE CLAIM]` |
| Close | `:::tip[TAKEAWAY]` (one paragraph) **or** `## Where I land` |
| Optional | `:::info[Builds on]` |

**Examples:** `policy-governed-agent-runtime`, `retrieval-is-a-governed-action`, `ai-observability-in-enterprise`, `rag-is-not-a-database`, `hallucination-system-design`

### 3. Concept primer

**When:** defines one idea before a how-to (what is agentic loop, what is intent router).

| Position | Required |
| --- | --- |
| Open | `:::tip[THE CLAIM]` + `## The bottom line first` (4-6 bullets) |
| Close | `## Key takeaways` (3-5 bullets) **or** `:::tip[TAKEAWAY]` + `:::info[Builds on]` |
| Body | Link to design/how-to insight where one exists |

**Examples:** `what-is-agentic-loop`, `what-is-intent-router`

### 4. Explainer

**When:** teaches a mechanism in stages (LLM lifecycle, training math).

| Position | Required |
| --- | --- |
| Open | Short intro; `:::tip[THE CLAIM]` optional |
| Body | `:::tip[TAKEAWAY]` per major stage/section where helpful |
| Close | `## Final takeaway` **or** final `:::tip[TAKEAWAY]` |
| Avoid | Generic `## Key takeaways` that repeats stage tips |

**Examples:** `how-llm-work-under-the-hood`, `before-training-an-llm`

### 5. Executive / long-form

**When:** boardroom or program-level framing with numbered sections.

| Position | Required |
| --- | --- |
| Open | `## The bottom line first` (4-6 bullets) |
| Close | Action section (e.g. questions to ask, maturity model, build series link) |
| Avoid | `## Key takeaways` that duplicates the opening bullets |

**Examples:** `eval-engineering-control-system-trustworthy-ai`

## Picking the type

| Signal in title or intent | Type |
| --- | --- |
| "how to choose", "vs", "options", "design guide" | Decision guide |
| "one request", "end to end", "architecture breakdown" | Architecture breakdown |
| "what is", "why it matters" (concept, not how-to) | Concept primer |
| Stages, lifecycle, "under the hood", worked examples | Explainer |
| Executive, maturity, "questions to ask", numbered program | Executive |

When unsure, prefer **architecture breakdown** for trace/wire articles and **decision guide** for comparison matrices.

## Before finishing

1. Classify the article (one type).
2. Confirm opening and closing match the type table.
3. Remove duplicate Summary/Key takeaways/TAKEAWAY blocks.
4. Key takeaways bullets: **decision-oriented**, not a prose recap of every section.
5. Confirm `image:` frontmatter, hero `![...](./…png)`, and the PNG file exist in the article folder.
